  <description type="morphology">Stems prostrate to decumbent or ± erect; herbage finely and closely grayish-arachnoid-tomentose or glabrous, minutely stipitate-glandular. Leaf blades narrowly oblanceolate, 5–22 × 2–4 mm, not thick-fleshy, margins entire or with 1–2 pairs of teeth distally. Heads in corymbiform to loose, paniculiform arrays. Corollas 5–6.5 mm. Cypselae 2.3–3.6 mm. 2n = 24.</description>
